  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Creating development plans and forecasting sales targets and growth projections</li>\n  <li>Identifying market opportunities through meetings, networking and other channels</li>\n  <li>Meeting existing and potential clients and building positive relationships</li>\n  <li>Liaising with colleagues to develop sales and marketing strategies</li>\n  <li>Preparing financial projections and sales targets</li>\n  <li>Attending events such as exhibitions and conferences</li>\n  <li>Preparing sales presentations and participating in sales meetings</li>\n  <li>Present sales reports and realistic forecasts to the management team</li>\n  <li>Recruit sales personnel, set objectives, train and coach them, and monitor their performance</li>\n  <li>Ensure that Sales targets are met by holding daily check-ins with the sales team to set objectives and monitor progress</li>\n  <li>Develop plans to use new technologies to improve business processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in any discipline</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of offline Sales experience from an e-commerce or retail background, with experience leading a sales team</li>\n  <li>Strong problem-solving, strategic, and analytical capabilities</li>\n  <li>Flexible and adapt to work in an exciting start-up environment</li>\n</ul>",
